data_ptsd %>%
mutate(fut2_4_cat = case_when(
    fut2 == 1 ~ 1, # certainly -> probablemente
    fut2 == 2 ~ 1, # probably  -> probablemente
    fut2 == 3 ~ 2, # undecided -> no lo se
    fut2 == 4 ~ 3, # probably not  -> probablemente no
    fut2 == 5 ~ 4  # certainly not -> no
    )) %>%
with(., table(fut2_4_cat)) %>%
barplot(.,
    col  = "#CAFF70", 
    main = "Presuncin de guerra civil segn civiles",
    xlab = "Sensacin de probabilidad de otra guerra civil dentro de 10 aos",
    names.arg = 
    c("probablemente",
        "no lo se",
        "probablemente no",
        "no"),
    ylab = "Frecuencia",

)

#repito frmula de disp
data_ptsd$disp = with(data_ptsd, rowMeans(cbind(for1,for5,for6), na.rm=TRUE))

#t test

t.test(formula = disp ~ war7,
data = data_ptsd,
alternative = c("two.sided"),
mu = 0,
paired = FALSE,
var.equal = TRUE,
conf.level = 0.95)
## 
##  Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  disp by war7
## t = -0.12212, df = 98, p-value = 0.9031

## sample estimates:
## mean in group 0 mean in group 1

data_model %>%

summarize(
  media = mean(anxiety, na.rm = TRUE),
  sd = sd(anxiety, na.rm = TRUE),
  n = n()
  ) %>%
